  "prompt": "How do I reset my Gmail Password?",
  "response": "If you need to reset your Gmail password, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Visit the Gmail Sign-In Page:**\n   - Go to the Gmail sign-in page at [gmail.com](https://mail.google.com).\n\n2. **Click on \"Forgot password?\":**\n   - Enter your email address and click \"Next.\"\n   - On the password entry page, click on \"Forgot password?\"\n\n3. **Verify Your Identity:**\n   - Google will prompt you to verify your identity. This might involve receiving a code via SMS or email, answering security questions, or confirming recent account activity.\n\n4. **Follow Instructions:**\n   - Depending on the verification method you choose or are provided, follow the instructions to verify your identity. Once you've successfully verified your identity, you'll be allowed to reset your password.\n\n5. **Create a New Password:**\n   - Enter a new password. Make sure it is strong, consisting of a mix of letters, numbers, and symbols.\n\n6. **Finalize the Process:**\n   - After setting your new password, you may be asked to review your security settings. Update any recovery options to ensure you can easily reset your password in the future.\n\n7. **Sign In:**\n   - Use your new password to sign in to your Gmail account.\n\nAlways ensure that your recovery options (such as your phone number and recovery email address) are up to date in your Google account settings. This will make it easier to reset your password in the future if needed.",
